<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Surge" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Surge,</orth> a large wave: <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.114" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.114" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 114</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tn 5.236" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 236</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 1, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.96" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 96</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.2.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 2, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.442" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 442</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.221" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 221</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.1.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 1, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 3.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. III, 1, 1</bibl>. Only once in prose, in a passage justly suspected: <cit><quote>to be thrown into the Thames, and cooled, glowing hot, in that s., like a horse-shoe,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.5.123" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 5, 123</bibl></cit> (Capell proposes <emph>forge,</emph> with little probability).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>